C++ class 'sys_stat' encapsulates functionality for system
statistics in Linux.

This class reads information from the /proc file system.
For further information, see man 5 proc.

Files:
------
sys_stat.h		Implements the
sys_stat.cpp		C++ class 'sys_stat'

test_sys_stat.cpp	Test application

Makefile		Makefile for this project

README		This file

Example output from test application:
-------------------------------------
CPU load [%]   = 1.500000
IRQ      [-]   = 337
Mem used [KB]  = 4242244
Uptime   [sec] = 678221

CPU load [%]   = 1.253133
IRQ      [-]   = 321
Mem used [KB]  = 4242244
Uptime   [sec] = 678222

CPU load [%]   = 1.253133
IRQ      [-]   = 358
Mem used [KB]  = 4242244
Uptime   [sec] = 678223

How to create a CPU load with a bash command:
---------------------------------------------
dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/null
while true; do true; done
